description.narrative: The Knowledge Management Services (KMS) Project provides support to the US Agency for International Development (USAID) Bureau for Global Health, and through this Bureau, to other USAID units working in health-related programs. KMS carries out activities in support of the strategic priorities for U.S. assistance in health, including: HIV/AIDS, Maternal and Child Health, Family Planning and Reproductive Health, Malaria, Tuberculosis, Other Public Health Threats, Avian and Pandemic Influenza, Nutrition, and Orphans and Vulnerable Children.
